title: Cashew Crusted Stuffed Tilapia
summary: Cashew Crusted Stuffed Tilapian is a pescatarian recipe with 1 servings. One portion of this dish contains approximately 187g of protein, 73g of fat, and a total of 2082 calories. For $17.2 per serving, this recipe covers 80% of your daily requirements of vitamins and minerals. A mixture of apricot, onion, garlic salt, and a handful of other ingredients are all it takes to make this recipe so yummy. To use up the cashew you could follow this main course with the Dark Chocolate Cashew Pudding with Candied Cashew Crunch as a dessert. It works well as a pricey main course. It is brought to you by Recipezaar. Only a few people made this recipe, and 1 would say it hit the spot. From preparation to the plate, this recipe takes around 1 hour and 5 minutes. All things considered, we decided this recipe deserves a spoonacular score of 80%. This score is solid. Try Cashew Crusted Stuffed Tilapia, Cashew-crusted Tilapia With Wild Rice, and Orange Cashew Rice {With Baked Tilapia} for similar recipes.

winePairing.pairingText: Pinot Grigio, Gruener Veltliner, and Pinot Noir are great choices for Tilapia. Fish is as diverse as wine, so it's hard to pick wines that go with every fish. A crisp white wine, such as a pinot grigio or Grüner Veltliner, will suit any delicately flavored white fish. Meaty, strongly flavored fish such as salmon and tuna can even handle a light red wine, such as a pinot noir. The La Fiera Pinot Grigio with a 4 out of 5 star rating seems like a good match. It costs about 7 dollars per bottle.

productMatches.title: La Fiera Pinot Grigio
productMatches.description: This wine has a light straw color with green tints. It has a light floral and fruity bouquet featuring apples and pears. The palate is bright, fresh and dry showing nice balance and a lingering acidity perfect for a variety of lighter cuisine.Blend: 100% Pinot Grigio

instructions: Combine all Cashew Crust ingredients in a small bowl and mix well.Rinse tilapia and pat dry.Whisk egg white in a small bowl and pour onto a small plate.Lightly flour one side of the tilapia fillets (fish should be covered in a fine dust layer of flour).Dredge floured side of fillet in egg white and then in Cashew Crust mixture.Set coated fillets (crust side up) on waxed paper and let set.Meanwhile, mix all the stuffing ingredients in a medium bowl.Carefully turn tilapia fillets over and squeeze lemon juice on fillets.Spread Stuffing evenly over fillet and fold so that the thicker side is on top (Use toothpicks to hold together if your fillets are small).Place in buttered baking dish and replace any crust that was wiped away.Cook at 350 degrees for 20 - 25 minutes.
